xgs360028fSystemTimeManualClockSource.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualClockSource
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualClockSource.description: default: 0, 0 : Use Local Settings, 1 : Use NTP Server.

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualLocaltime.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualLocaltime
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualLocaltime.description: Get/Set the system time of the device. The input format is 'Year-Month-Day Hour:Minute:Second'. ex: 2011-01-01 05:43:05 means 2011/1/1 - 05:43:05 . The value range: Year : 2010 - 2090, Mouth : 1 - 12, Day : 1 - 31, Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59, Sec : 0 - 59.

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualTimeZoneOffset.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualTimeZoneOffset
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualTimeZoneOffset.description: Get/Set the NTP Time Zone. The value range is between -720 and 780 (minutes).

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualTimeSetOffset.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualTimeSetOffset
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualTimeSetOffset.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time. The value range is between 1 and 1440 (minutes), Default : 60 (minutes).

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsBydatesFrom
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Start time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Year-Month-Day Hour:Minute'. ex: 2011-01-01 05:43 means 2011/1/1 - 05:43 . The value range: Year : 2010 - 2090, Mouth : 1 - 12, Day : 1 - 31, Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsBydatesTo
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the End time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Year-Month-Day Hour:Minute'. ex: 2011-01-01 05:43 means 2011/1/1 - 05:43 . The value range: Year : 2010 - 2090, Mouth : 1 - 12, Day : 1 - 31, Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringDayFrom
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Day From. 0 : Sun, 1 : Mon, 2 : Tue, 3 : Wed, 4 : Thu, 5 : Fri, 6 : Sat.

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringWeekFrom
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Week From. 1 : first week, 2, 3, 4, 5 : last week

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringMonthFrom
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Month From. 1 : Jan, 2 : Feb, 3 : Mar, 4 : Apr, 5 : May, 6 : Jun, 7 : Jul, 8 : Aug, 9 : Sep, 10 : Oct, 11 : Nov, 12 : Dec.

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringTimeFrom
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Start time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Hour:Minute'. ex: 05:43. The value range: Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringDayTo
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Day To. 0 : Sun, 1 : Mon, 2 : Tue, 3 : Wed, 4 : Thu, 5 : Fri, 6 : Sat.

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringWeekTo
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Week To. 1 : first week, 2, 3, 4, 5 : last week

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringMonthTo
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Daylight Saving Time Month To. 1 : Jan, 2 : Feb, 3 : Mar, 4 : Apr, 5 : May, 6 : Jun, 7 : Jul, 8 : Aug, 9 : Sep, 10 : Oct, 11 : Nov, 12 : Dec.

xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSavingsRecurringTimeTo
xgs360028fSystemTimeManualDaylightSaving.description: Get/Set the Start time of By dates Daylight Savings. The input format is 'Hour:Minute'. ex: 05:43. The value range: Hour : 0 - 23, Minute : 0 - 59.

xgs360028fSystemTimeNTPIndex.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeNTPIndex
xgs360028fSystemTimeNTPIndex.description: The index of the ntp entry.

xgs360028fSystemTimeNTPServer.name: xgs360028fSystemTimeNTPServer
xgs360028fSystemTimeNTPServer.description: Get/Set the NTP Time Server1. You can use the IP address or domain name.

xgs360028fSystemAccountUserCreate.name: xgs360028fSystemAccountUserCreate
xgs360028fSystemAccountUserCreate.description: default: 0 0 : None (read only) 1 : Create a user account

xgs360028fSyslogLevel.name: xgs360028fSyslogLevel
xgs360028fSyslogLevel.description: default: 6 (Info) 0: Emergency 1: Alert 2: Critical 3: Error 4: Warning 5: Notice 6: Info 7: Debug

xgs360028fGetCommunity.name: xgs360028fGetCommunity
xgs360028fGetCommunity.description: Get/Set the get-community of the SNMP.

xgs360028fSetCommunityMode.name: xgs360028fSetCommunityMode
xgs360028fSetCommunityMode.description: Get/Set the set-community mode of the SNMP. default : 1, 0: disable, 1: enable.

xgs360028fSetCommunity.name: xgs360028fSetCommunity
xgs360028fSetCommunity.description: Get/Set the set-community of the SNMP.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfTable.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfTable
xgs360028fTrapHostConfTable.description: A list of trap host entry. The numbers of entries are given by the value of xgs360028fTrapHostConfNumber.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfEntry.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfEntry
xgs360028fTrapHostConfEntry.description: This is the entry information for trap host.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfIndex.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfIndex
xgs360028fTrapHostConfIndex.description: The index of the trap host entry.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfVersion.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfVersion
xgs360028fTrapHostConfVersion.description: The version of the Trap PDU. Version : 2(SNMPv2c), 3(SNMPv3)

xgs360028fTrapHostConfIPType.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfIPType
xgs360028fTrapHostConfIPType.description: Server IP Type. Default: 4, 4 : IPv4, 6 : IPv6.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfIP.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfIP
xgs360028fTrapHostConfIP.description: This is the IP of the trap host.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfPort.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfPort
xgs360028fTrapHostConfPort.description: This is the receiving-port number of the trap host. range : 1 - 65535.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfCommunity.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfCommunity
xgs360028fTrapHostConfCommunity.description: The community/security name for the trap PDU.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfSeverityLevel.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfSeverityLevel
xgs360028fTrapHostConfSeverityLevel.description: The Severity Level. 0 : Emerg, 1 : Alert, 2 : Crit, 3 : Error, 4 : Warning, 5 : Notice, 6 : Info, 7 : Debug.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfSecurityLevel.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfSecurityLevel
xgs360028fTrapHostConfSecurityLevel.description: The Security Level, NoAuthNoPriv, AuthNoPriv, and AuthPriv. 1 : NoAuthNoPriv, 2 : AuthNoPriv, 3 : AuthPriv. Privacy protocol will be configured as 'DES' automatically if security level is 3(AuthPriv).

xgs360028fTrapHostConfAuthPtc.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfAuthPtc
xgs360028fTrapHostConfAuthPtc.description: Authentication Protocol, there are SHA and MD5 supported presently. 1 : MD5, 2 : SHA.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfAuthPassword.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfAuthPassword
xgs360028fTrapHostConfAuthPassword.description: Authentication Password, is used for authenticating. The return value is always '********'. If the authentication protocol is MD5, the length of password should be 8 ~ 32 characters. If the authentication protocol is SHA, the length of password should be 8 ~ 40 characters.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfPrivPtc.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfPrivPtc
xgs360028fTrapHostConfPrivPtc.description: This is the Privacy Protocol, which is used in AuthPriv. Only supports DES. An empty string will be returned if the security level is not 3(AuthPriv). 1 : DES.

xgs360028fTrapHostConfPrivPassword.name: xgs360028fTrapHostConfPrivPassword
xgs360028fTrapHostConfPrivPassword.description: The password is Privacy Key. The return value is always '********'. This Key must be more than 8 characters, and less than 32 characters.

xgs360028fPortConfCurrentSpeed.name: xgs360028fPortConfCurrentSpeed
xgs360028fPortConfCurrentSpeed.description: The current link speed of the port.

xgs360028fPortConfSpeed.name: xgs360028fPortConfSpeed
xgs360028fPortConfSpeed.description: default: 1, 0: disable state, 1: auto, 2: 10 Half, 3: 10 Full, 4: 100 Half, 5: 100 Full, 6: 1G full, only 'Dual Media' port have 7-11 option. Dual Media port default: 7, 7: SFP_Auto_AMS, 8: 100FX_AMS, 9: 1000X_AMS, 10: 100FX, 11: 1000X

xgs360028fPortConfExcessiveCollisionMode.name: xgs360028fPortConfExcessiveCollisionMode
xgs360028fPortConfExcessiveCollisionMode.description: default: 0, Excessive Collision Mode : 0: Discard, 1: Restart, 2: not support.

xgs360028fPortConfPowerControl.name: xgs360028fPortConfPowerControl
xgs360028fPortConfPowerControl.description: default: 0, PowerControl : 0: disable, 1: Actiphy, 2: Dynamic (perfectReach), 3: Enable, 4: not support.

xgs360028fPortConfDescription.name: xgs360028fPortConfDescription
xgs360028fPortConfDescription.description: Interface specific description. Up to 47 characters describing this interface.

xgs360028fGARPStatisticsTable.name: xgs360028fGARPStatisticsTable
xgs360028fGARPStatisticsTable.description: Show the basic GARP port statistics.

xgs360028fGARPStatisticsPeerMAC.name: xgs360028fGARPStatisticsPeerMAC
xgs360028fGARPStatisticsPeerMAC.description: Peer MAC is MAC address of the neighbour Switch from with GARP frame is received.

xgs360028fMirrorMode.name: xgs360028fMirrorMode
xgs360028fMirrorMode.description: default: 0 0: disable 1: enable 2: rx only 3: tx only Setting Tx mirroring for analyzer port has no effect. Tx mirroring ignored

xgs360028fACLPortsConfPortRedirect.description: default: 0 0: Disable range : 0 - end port number

xgs360028fACLPortsConfCounter.name: xgs360028fACLPortsConfCounter
xgs360028fACLPortsConfCounter.description: Counts the number of frames that match this ACE.

xgs360028fACLACECreate.name: xgs360028fACLACECreate
xgs360028fACLACECreate.description: default: 0 0 : None (read only) 1 : Create an ACE entry

xgs360028fACLACEID.name: xgs360028fACLACEID
xgs360028fACLACEID.description: If the ACE ID is specified and an entry with this ACE ID already exists, the ACE will be modified. Otherwise, a new ACE will be added. range : 1 - 256.

xgs360028fACLACENextID.name: xgs360028fACLACENextID
xgs360028fACLACENextID.description: If the next ACE ID is non zero, the ACE will be placed before this ACE in the list. If the next ACE ID is zero, the ACE will be placed last in the list. range : 0 - 256.

xgs360028fACLACEIngressPort.name: xgs360028fACLACEIngressPort
xgs360028fACLACEIngressPort.description: Indicates the ingress port of the ACE. Possible values are: All: The ACE will match all ingress port. Port: The ACE will match a specific ingress port.Format: 1,3,6.

xgs360028fACLACEFrameType.name: xgs360028fACLACEFrameType
xgs360028fACLACEFrameType.description: 0: any, 1: arp, 2: etype, 3: icmp, 4: ipv4, 5: tcp, 6: udp.

xgs360028fACLACEDenyPortRedirect.name: xgs360028fACLACEDenyPortRedirect
xgs360028fACLACEDenyPortRedirect.description: Frames that hit the ACE are redirected to the port number specified here. Disabled: indicates that the port redirect operation is disabled. Port Format: 1,3,6.

xgs360028fACLACELogging.name: xgs360028fACLACELogging
xgs360028fACLACELogging.description: default: 0, 0: disable - Frames matching the ACE are not logged. 1: enable - Frames matching the ACE are stored in the system log.

xgs360028fACLACEShutdown.name: xgs360028fACLACEShutdown
xgs360028fACLACEShutdown.description: default: 0, 0: disable - Port shut down is disabled for the AC. 1: enable - If a frame matches the ACE, the ingress port will be disabled.

xgs360028fACLACEVLANTagPriority.name: xgs360028fACLACEVLANTagPriority
xgs360028fACLACEVLANTagPriority.description: Specify the tag priority for this ACE. The tag priority can't be set when 802.1Q Tagged is disabled default: 8, 8: Any, range : 0 - 8

xgs360028fACLACEVLANVID.name: xgs360028fACLACEVLANVID
xgs360028fACLACEVLANVID.description: Specify the VLAN ID filter for this ACE. The vid can't be set when 802.1Q Tagged is disabled. default: 0, 0: Any - No VLAN ID filter is specified. range : 0 - 4094

xgs360028fACLACEEtherType.name: xgs360028fACLACEEtherType
xgs360028fACLACEEtherType.description: 0: Any - Any but excluding 0x0800(IPv4) 0x0806(ARP) and 0x86DD(IPv6). range : 0 or 1536(0x0600)- 65535(0xffff).

xgs360028fACLACESMAC.name: xgs360028fACLACESMAC
xgs360028fACLACESMAC.description: Configure source MAC address for this ACE. <mac-address>: A frame that hits this ACE matches this source MAC address value. Any: Don't care.

xgs360028fACLACEDMACType.name: xgs360028fACLACEDMACType
xgs360028fACLACEDMACType.description: DMAC Type. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: Broadcast - Frame must be broadcast. 2: Unicast - Frame must be unicast. 3: Multicast - Frame must be multicast. 4: mac address range : 0 - 4

xgs360028fACLACEDMAC.name: xgs360028fACLACEDMAC
xgs360028fACLACEDMAC.description: Configure destination MAC address for this ACE. <mac-address>: A frame that hits this ACE matches this destination MAC address value. Any: Don't care. Broadcast: Frame must be broadcast. Unicast: Frame must be unicast. Multicast: Frame must be multicast.

xgs360028fACLACEArpOpcode.name: xgs360028fACLACEArpOpcode
xgs360028fACLACEArpOpcode.description: Configure ARP opcode for this ACE. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: arp. 2: rarp. 3: other. 4: No data. range : 0 - 3

xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsRequestReply.name: xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsRequestReply
xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsRequestReply.description: Specify the available ARP/RARP opcode (OP) flag for this ACE. default: 2, 0: Frame must have ARP Reply or RARP Reply OP flag. 1: Frame must have ARP Request or RARP Request OP flag set. 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsArpSmac.name: xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsArpSmac
xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsArpSmac.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their sender hardware address field (SHA) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP frames where SHA is not equal to the SMAC address. 1: ARP frames where SHA is equal to the SMAC address. 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsRarpDmac.name: xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsRarpDmac
xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsRarpDmac.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their target hardware address field (THA) settings. default: 2, 0: RARP frames where THA is not equal to the DMAC address. 1: RARP frames where THA is equal to the DMAC address. 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsLength.name: xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsLength
xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsLength.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their ARP/RARP hardware address length (HLN) and protocol address length (PLN) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP/RARP frames where the HLN is not equal to Ethernet(0x06) or the (PLN) is not equal to IPv4(0x04). 1: ARP/RARP frames where the HLN is equal to Ethernet (0x06) and the (PLN) is equal to IPv4(0x04). 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsIp.name: xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsIp
xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsIp.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their ARP/RARP hardware address space (HRD) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP/RARP frames where the HLD is not equal to Ethernet(1). 1: ARP/RARP frames where the HLD is equal to Ethernet(1). 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsEthernet.name: xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsEthernet
xgs360028fACLACEArpFlagsEthernet.description: Specify whether frames can hit the action according to their ARP/RARP protocol address space (PRO) settings. default: 2, 0: ARP/RARP frames where the PRO is not equal to IP\n(0x800). 1: ARP/RARP frames where the PRO is equal to IP(0x800). 2: Any - Don't care. 3: No data. range : 0 - 2

xgs360028fACLACESIPType.name: xgs360028fACLACESIPType
xgs360028fACLACESIPType.description: Configure source IP address for this ACE. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: IP Address. 2: No data. range : 0 - 1

xgs360028fACLACESIPIPAddress.name: xgs360028fACLACESIPIPAddress
xgs360028fACLACESIPIPAddress.description: A frame that hits this ACE matches this source IP address value.

xgs360028fACLACESIPNetworkPrefix.name: xgs360028fACLACESIPNetworkPrefix
xgs360028fACLACESIPNetworkPrefix.description: Network prefix. default: 32, 0: No data. range : 1 - 32

xgs360028fACLACEDIPType.name: xgs360028fACLACEDIPType
xgs360028fACLACEDIPType.description: Configure destination IP address for this ACE. default: 0, 0: Any - Don't care. 1: IP Address. 2: No data. range : 0 - 1

xgs360028fACLACEDIPIPAddress.name: xgs360028fACLACEDIPIPAddress
xgs360028fACLACEDIPIPAddress.description: A frame that hits this ACE matches this destination IP address value.

xgs360028fACLACEDIPNetworkPrefix.name: xgs360028fACLACEDIPNetworkPrefix
xgs360028fACLACEDIPNetworkPrefix.description: Network prefix. default: 32, 0: No data. range : 1 - 32

xgs360028fACLACEIPProtocol.name: xgs360028fACLACEIPProtocol
xgs360028fACLACEIPProtocol.description: Configure IP protocol for this ACE. default: 256, 256: Any - Don't care. 257: No data. range : 0 - 256
